BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 5 May--Following today's meeting with U.S. 
Trade Secretary Ronald Brown, Prime Minister Waldemar Pawlak 
said that he hopes better conditions for full economic 
cooperation between Poland and the United States will be 
created. The prime minister stressed that the best way for 
meeting Poland's obligations toward the United States is the 
development of trade between the two countries. 
  Brown described the talk with the prime minister as 
constructive. "We spoke about how trade and investment 
cooperation between Poland and the United States could be 
expanded," he said. 

